            "answer": "<p>EmailÂ <a href=\"mailto:feedback@xeroshoes.com\">feedback@xeroshoes.com</a>Â if you have a suggestion or request for a specific shoe, color, or size. The more demand we have, the greater our ability to make more shoes (this includes making menâ€™s versions of our womenâ€™s shoes and visa versa).</p><p>The womenâ€™s styles will fit more narrow than the menâ€™s. If you are a man with a narrow foot, then you may be prefer the â€œwomenâ€™sâ€ sizes. If you are a woman with a wider foot, then you may want to try the â€œmenâ€™sâ€ styles.</p><p>The difference in length between menâ€™s and womenâ€™s closed toe shoes is 1.5 sizes.</p><p>Below is a size conversion chart:<br/><br/><strong>Menâ€™s Size</strong></p><ul><li>6.5</li><li>7</li><li>7.5</li><li>8</li><li>8.5</li><li>9</li><li>9.5</li></ul><p><strong>Womenâ€™sSize</strong></p><ul><li>8</li><li>8.5</li><li>9</li><li>9.5</li><li>10</li><li>10.5</li><li>11<br/></li></ul><p>Our sandals, since they come in â€œwhole sizesâ€ only have only a 1 size difference between styles. A menâ€™s 8, for example, would be comparable in length to a womenâ€™s 9.</p>",
            "answer_html": ""
          }
        },
        "faq_subitem_9BN7ed": {
          "type": "faq_subitem",
          "settings": {
            "parent_title": "Product Questions - Before you buy",
            "title": "Will you make more kidâ€™s sizes and styles?",
            "answer": "<p>Currently, our kids sizes range from 12 to youth 4 (Y4).</p><p>From there, a womenâ€™s 6 will be a half size larger than the Y4.</p><p>That means that if your kid wears a youth 5 or up, they can fit into our womenâ€™s sizes.</p><p>And if you want to recommend a new/different size or style, emailÂ <a href=\"mailto:feedback@xeroshoes.com\">feedback@xeroshoes.com</a></p>",
            "answer_html": ""
