        "faq_subitem_nNn6Dh": {
          "type": "faq_subitem",
          "settings": {
            "parent_title": "About the shoes you received",
            "title": "How do I know if these are the right size?",
            "answer": "<p>The simplest answer is: Do they feel right?</p><p>Sizing is largely about personal preference. You could take 3 people with identical feet, put them in the same shoe, and theyâ€™d have 3 different opinions about how the shoe fits.</p><p>Some people think you need a lot of room in front of your toes. This is true for shoes with thick midsoles, but not with Xero Shoes (when thicker shoes bend, the â€œinsideâ€ shortens faster than the outsideâ€¦ like what happens when you bend a phone book).</p><p>Some people like their toes to lightly touch the front of the shoe because it gives them additional feedback.</p><p>We recommend wearing the shoes indoors for a bit to see how they feel (remember, if you need to return or exchange, the product must be in â€œnew and unwornâ€ condition).</p><p>If youâ€™re a woman with a wider foot, you may be more comfortable in a â€œmenâ€™sâ€ style. And if youâ€™re a man with a narrower foot, you may like a â€œwomenâ€™sâ€ style better.</p><p>If you have other questions about fit, give us a call â€” 303.447.3100 or 1-800.499.8880</p>",
            "answer_html": ""
          }
